5: Heh, that all your underlings got?
11:
Haven't you had enough? There's no
point in continuing the fight.
14:
I-I'm not finished yet! Shuilong, it's
your turn!
25:
Yet another fine mess you've made.
What happened to not needing my
services?
28:
L-let's agree to a new contract! Take
care of these pests for me—
35: Haha, I'll take my usual rate then.
38: And stay out of my way while I work.
57:
I thought the Crimson Blades were
supposed to be tough. Perhaps I
was wrong to get my hopes up.
79: What is that sword of yours, boy?
88:
So you haven't noticed yet. Never
mind then.
91: Show me you know how to use it.
95:
Yes, that's it, Shuilong! Drive them
into a corner!
102:
Look me in the eyes. What. Are. You.
Doing?
107:
Did you not hear me earlier? When I
say stay out of my way, I MEAN it.
114:
You've completely ruined the mood.
What a killjoy.
117: Well, boy. What do you want to do?
125:
My contract was breached, so I'm
back to being a freelancer.
129:
For a limited time only, I'll kill them all
for a discounted price.
132:
Why? Because I feel like it. Now tell
me if you want the deal before I
change my mind.
137:
First of all, no killing allowed!
Secondly, I can only pay you in free
meals—dinner only, to be specific.
147:
Those are my two conditions! Take it
or leave it!
150:
Damn you all to the depths of the
ocean! Kill them! Kill them all!
155: Fine then. I'll spare your measly lives.
161: So... Why are you following us?
164:
You never decided on the duration
of our contract.
169:
...Don't tell me you're actually fine
with following us around and being
paid in FOOD.
174:
You never said how much food. I
expect you to prepare dinner for me
every day.
176:
Enough chatter. Take me to your
ship.
181:
I must insist that we cut ties with her
immediately. She is a menace.
185:
You don't say. I'd rather make
friends with a kraken than take her
home.
187:
Doesn't look like she'll take no for an
answer though. We should call for
some backup before we cut loose
and run.
192:
H-hold on, before we do anything
hasty... She made a contract with us,
remember? Judging by her
behavior so far, she's serious about
honoring it.
197:
You crazy? Or did you hit your head
too hard back there? She tried to kill
you!
202: The contract is law for you... right?
207: It's my policy to honor it.
218:
Haha... Hahaha! You must be the
greatest employers I've ever worked
with!
221:
To think there's a platform with
access to all the strongest warriors
across different worlds!
224:
Who do you wish me to kill? Which
world are they in?
227:
We went over this, didn't we? No
killing allowed.
231:
No time limit on our contract either,
and you're paid in food. Those were
the terms.
243:
You better not miss a single dinner
from now on, then.
245:
Or else you'll see what happens
when you breach our contract.
249:
Don't worry, I won't forget. By the
way, we're having plain curry tonight.
253:
I can't even... This one might be too
far, even by our standards.
